The spiral is the usual Ulam spiral:  

\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
5&4&3\\
6&1&2\\
7&8&9
\end{array}
\]

Let a point \((x,y)\) have coordinates with the centre \(1\) at \((0,0)\).
For a point \((x,y)\) set  

\[
k=\max(|x|,|y|),\qquad t=2k+1,\qquad T=t^{2}.
\]

\(T\) is the number at the bottom‑right corner \((k,-k)\) of the ring of
radius \(k\).
The number at any point of that ring is

\[
N(x,y)=
\begin{cases}
T-(k-x)            & y=-k \\[2pt]
T-2k-(y+k)        & x=-k \\[2pt]
T-4k-(x+k)        & y= k \\[2pt]
T-6k-(k-y)        & x= k .
\end{cases}
\tag{1}
\]

---

### Position of 2026  

\[
\sqrt{2026}\approx45.01,\qquad 45^{2}=2025.
\]

Thus 2025 is the last number of the ring with \(k=22\)
(\(t=45\)).  
The next number, \(2026\), starts the next ring (\(k=23\)):
\[
2026\text{ is at }(23,-22).
\]

---

### The eight neighbours

| coordinate \((x,y)\) | \(k\) | side | \(N(x,y)\) |
|----------------------|------|------|------------|
| \((22,-23)\) | 23 | bottom | \(2209-(23-22)=2208\) |
| \((23,-23)\) | 23 | bottom | \(2209-(23-23)=2209\) |
| \((24,-23)\) | 24 | right  | \((2·24+1)^2-6·24-(24-(-23))=2210\) |
| \((22,-22)\) | 22 | bottom‑right corner | \(2025\) |
| \((24,-22)\) | 24 | right  | \(2401-6·24-(24-(-22))=2211\) |
| \((22,-21)\) | 22 | right  | \(2025-6·22-(22-(-21))=1850\) |
| \((23,-21)\) | 23 | right  | \(2209-6·23-(23-(-21))=2027\) |
| \((24,-21)\) | 24 | right  | \(2401-6·24-(24-(-21))=2212\) |

---

### Summation

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sum}&=2208+2209+2210+2025+2211+1850+2027+2212\\
&=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
